name: poe-ladder
description: Ladder rank overlay for Path of Exile

releases.name: 1.0.5 - Toolbar Mode
releases.body: Recent windows update caused the ladder overlay to force the taskbar on top of Path of Exile for users running Windows 10. The window is now classified as a toolbar when activated and no longer causes this issue.

releases.name: 1.0.4 - Electron Update
releases.body: - Updated from Electron v1.3.2 to v1.4.2. This may solve taskbar related issues some users were having on windows 10

releases.name: Defaults and Taskbar
releases.body:
- Remembers last used settings
- No longer displays icon in the taskbar while tracking is active. This is a possible fix to reported scenarios where the taskbar would stay on top the Path of Exile client while running in borderless window mode.

releases.name: Down is Up
releases.body:
Small aesthetic fix
- Negative numbers indicating an increase in rank are highlighted in green
- Positive numbers indicating a loss of rank are highlighted in red

releases.name: Exp and Commas
releases.body:
Fixed two minor issues:
- **Minimum EP:** changed to **Minimum Exp:** to be more consistent with the in game abbreviation
- Experience points digits are now grouped appropriately (ie. 123,456,789 instead of 123456789)

releases.name: v1.0.0 - Initial Release
releases.body:
Initial release. The Path of Exile ladder overlay displays
- Your character's overall rank
- Your character's class rank
- The minimum experience points required to place on the ladder (if not placed)
- The minimum level required to place on the ladder (if not placed)
